overview: The user initiated a code review for a sleep questionnaire
  application, requesting verification against documented acceptance criteria.
  The assistant conducted a thorough review of the codebase, examining core
  functionalities, questionnaire sections, conditional logic, sleep disorder
  detection, calculated metrics, report generation, and administrative features.
  The review concluded that the application largely met all major acceptance
  criteria, demonstrating a comprehensive and well-executed implementation.
  Minor observations included the combined "cocktails/beer" field, the method
  for social jetlag detection, and a suggestion for more explicit Non-24
  circadian rhythm disorder flagging. Overall, the application was found to
  align well with the specified requirements, including privacy and data
  collection protocols.
